15
00:02:47,814 --> 00:02:50,776
If we don't operate right now,
she's going into respiratory arrest.

16
00:02:51,359 --> 00:02:52,694
We'll try our best.

17
00:02:52,778 --> 00:02:54,821
Ms. Ko. I have to ask you
to wait out here.

18
00:02:58,867 --> 00:02:59,993
[sobs]

19
00:03:01,453 --> 00:03:05,582
WOORI TOGETHER MEDICAL CENTER

20
00:03:05,665 --> 00:03:07,417
CALLING
HUSBAND

21
00:03:09,044 --> 00:03:11,838
Come on, honey, pick up.

22
00:03:11,922 --> 00:03:13,465
Please. Hayun is…

23
00:03:16,468 --> 00:03:18,470
Why won't he pick up?

24
00:03:20,263 --> 00:03:21,932
Where on earth is he?

25
00:03:24,643 --> 00:03:25,644
[doctor] Blade.

26
00:03:30,732 --> 00:03:31,858
Bovie, please.

27
00:03:43,870 --> 00:03:44,955
[sniffles]

28
00:03:49,417 --> 00:03:50,544
[sobs]
STYLE
::cue()

29
00:03:59,761 --> 00:04:01,304
[monitor beeping]

30
00:04:04,849 --> 00:04:05,850
Vitals are dropping.

31
00:04:06,768 --> 00:04:07,936
Give me an amp of epi.

32
00:04:19,948 --> 00:04:21,950
Oh, please…

33
00:04:26,580 --> 00:04:27,664
[doctor] She's flatlining!

34
00:04:36,464 --> 00:04:38,717
The patient is flatlining.
Keep compressions going.

35
00:04:39,593 --> 00:04:40,802
Get the crash cart in here!

36
00:04:41,303 --> 00:04:43,305
[monitor flatlining]

37
00:04:43,388 --> 00:04:44,514
[gasps]

38
00:04:45,891 --> 00:04:47,517
[breathing shakily]

39
00:04:50,228 --> 00:04:52,439
[flatlining continues]

40
00:05:13,752 --> 00:05:16,296
[doctor] Ms. Ko, we're sorry.

41
00:05:17,255 --> 00:05:18,882
We did our best, but…

42
00:05:34,898 --> 00:05:36,566
[breathing heavily]

43
00:05:42,656 --> 00:05:44,115
[sobs]

44
00:05:48,703 --> 00:05:49,829
[sobs]

45
00:05:52,791 --> 00:05:55,168
[crying]

46
00:05:55,919 --> 00:05:57,128
[doctor] Dr. Kang.

47
00:05:57,212 --> 00:05:59,005
RESTRICTED AREA
AUTHORIZED PERSONNEL ONLY

48
00:06:16,064 --> 00:06:17,565
Where have you been?

49
00:06:23,488 --> 00:06:26,950
[crying]

50
00:06:33,623 --> 00:06:36,960
I said, where have you been?

51
00:06:44,843 --> 00:06:46,928
Where have you been?

52
00:06:51,891 --> 00:06:53,643
Answer me!

53
00:06:55,145 --> 00:06:57,772
Where the hell have you been?

54
00:06:59,566 --> 00:07:00,567
While…

55
00:07:04,028 --> 00:07:08,116
Where were you while our Hayun was dying?

56
00:07:17,250 --> 00:07:18,710
This is all your fault.

57
00:07:21,671 --> 00:07:23,381
It's all your fault.

58
00:07:24,674 --> 00:07:26,926
[inhales deeply, sobs]

59
00:07:29,429 --> 00:07:31,222
This whole thing is your fault.

60
00:07:35,518 --> 00:07:38,188
This is all your fault!

61
00:07:42,901 --> 00:07:47,822
THE HUSBAND
STYLE
::cue()

62
00:07:49,908 --> 00:07:52,285
SEONGJIN POLICE STATION

63
00:07:52,368 --> 00:07:54,370
[Dosik] How do you know the kidnapper?

64
00:07:55,789 --> 00:07:57,248
I don't know him.

65
00:07:58,208 --> 00:08:00,668
He showed up when I called for a driver.

66
00:08:00,752 --> 00:08:02,796
So you solicited

67
00:08:03,671 --> 00:08:05,507
a complete stranger to murder your wife?

68
00:08:06,174 --> 00:08:07,842
I never solicited anything.

69
00:08:07,926 --> 00:08:11,221
Mr. Kang, where's your accomplice?

70
00:08:11,721 --> 00:08:12,931
[stammers, sighs]

71
00:08:13,807 --> 00:08:15,934
I really don't know.
I didn't put him up to it.

72
00:08:16,017 --> 00:08:17,685
Tell us. You know where she is!

73
00:08:17,769 --> 00:08:20,772
I said I don't know! [panting]

74
00:08:20,855 --> 00:08:22,440
[Dosik] Your accomplice…

75
00:08:22,524 --> 00:08:25,693
He's way more dangerous than you think.

76
00:08:25,777 --> 00:08:27,904
You're going to end up
taking the fall alone.

77
00:08:28,530 --> 00:08:33,034
Just how many times do I have to tell you?

78
00:08:33,785 --> 00:08:35,829
You're losing time here!

79
00:08:36,704 --> 00:08:40,583
Do you have any idea
what a waste of time this is?

80
00:08:41,084 --> 00:08:44,295
This guy is a psycho!
My wife is in danger!

81
00:08:44,379 --> 00:08:45,380
Calm down, Mr. Kang.

82
00:08:45,463 --> 00:08:46,589
I'm serious!

83
00:08:47,132 --> 00:08:49,634
There's no time to be screwing around!

84
00:08:49,717 --> 00:08:50,718
Mr. Kang!

85
00:08:51,928 --> 00:08:54,889
[Taeju grunts, groans]

86
00:08:57,642 --> 00:08:59,018
[Dosik] Calm now?

87
00:09:01,312 --> 00:09:04,065
Wash your face off.
And freshen up a little.

88
00:09:04,149 --> 00:09:05,608
That one doesn't work.

89
00:09:05,692 --> 00:09:06,860
Use the next one.

90
00:09:09,070 --> 00:09:10,488
What the hell?

91
00:09:10,572 --> 00:09:14,909
[Hyeonsu] Man, it's about time
they fix this place up.

92
00:09:14,993 --> 00:09:16,494
Nothing works in here.

93
00:09:16,578 --> 00:09:18,121
[phone buzzing]

94
00:09:20,623 --> 00:09:22,250
Hey, Captain Kim.

95
00:09:22,333 --> 00:09:24,961
Yeah. It's been too long.

96
00:09:25,461 --> 00:09:27,338
Oh, that? Yeah, it was really helpful.

97
00:09:27,422 --> 00:09:28,548
Take your time, okay?

98
00:09:29,090 --> 00:09:32,510
Right, I was going to come and see you.

99
00:09:34,596 --> 00:09:36,931
-[employees chattering]
-[officer] Come on, not this again.

100
00:09:38,391 --> 00:09:40,310
What the hell, man?

101
00:09:40,393 --> 00:09:42,270
SEONGJIN POLICE STATION

102
00:09:42,353 --> 00:09:44,689
SAFE SEONGJIN, TRUSTED POLICE

103
00:09:45,815 --> 00:09:48,735
[Taeju] I didn't do it,
but everyone thinks I did.

104
00:09:50,320 --> 00:09:52,322
No one believes me.

105
00:09:53,406 --> 00:09:54,699
[stranger] Who would?

106
00:09:58,953 --> 00:10:00,246
No one believes you.

107
00:10:01,873 --> 00:10:04,125
Why would anyone believe you, Mr. Kang?

108
00:10:08,755 --> 00:10:10,173
Who are you?

109
00:10:14,969 --> 00:10:16,304
I said, who are you?

110
00:10:17,513 --> 00:10:22,644
I'm the only one who knows
you didn't plot your wife's death.

111
00:10:25,605 --> 00:10:26,606
What?

112
00:10:34,280 --> 00:10:35,365
Mr. Kang.

113
00:10:39,744 --> 00:10:40,745
Mr. Kang.

114
00:10:41,537 --> 00:10:42,789
Mr. Kang!

115
00:10:45,333 --> 00:10:48,169
-Mr. Kang!
-Oh, yes. I'm right here.

116
00:10:48,253 --> 00:10:49,796
Why didn't you answer any…

117
00:10:50,505 --> 00:10:51,673
You going to be a while?

118
00:10:52,173 --> 00:10:53,299
Little bit, yeah.

119
00:10:54,133 --> 00:10:56,552
Power's out, but don't panic.

120
00:10:56,636 --> 00:10:58,137
And make it quick.
STYLE
::cue()

121
00:10:58,221 --> 00:11:00,098
Okay, I got it. Sorry.

122
00:11:22,954 --> 00:11:23,955
So who are you?

123
00:11:27,917 --> 00:11:30,420
How do you know
I didn't have my wife kidnapped?

124
00:11:31,963 --> 00:11:35,258
What's important isn't how I know,

125
00:11:36,050 --> 00:11:38,177
but whether your wife is alive
or not right now.

126
00:11:40,096 --> 00:11:41,514
[Taeju] What?

127
00:11:41,597 --> 00:11:44,642
I doubt there's anyone you can trust
besides me right now.

128
00:11:46,853 --> 00:11:48,396
Who the hell are you?

129
00:11:49,814 --> 00:11:50,898
I told you.

130
00:11:51,607 --> 00:11:56,070
I'm the only one who knows
you didn't have your wife kidnapped.

131
00:11:57,613 --> 00:12:00,408
Or rather, I'm the only one
who can help you.

132
00:12:04,620 --> 00:12:05,621
So…

133
00:12:06,664 --> 00:12:09,500
Seyun is alive, right?

134
00:12:10,710 --> 00:12:12,128
Where is she right now?

135
00:12:13,004 --> 00:12:17,967
If you want to find your wife,
come to 543-7, Shinyu-dong by 11 p.m.

136
00:12:19,510 --> 00:12:20,803
What was that?

137
00:12:20,887 --> 00:12:21,888
If you don't,

138
00:12:22,805 --> 00:12:24,724
you may never get to see her again.

139
00:12:24,807 --> 00:12:29,228
[breathes shakily] Look, man.
I'm being held here as a suspect.

140
00:12:29,312 --> 00:12:31,356
How am I supposed to get there by 11 p.m.?

141
00:12:32,315 --> 00:12:33,691
Remember.

142
00:12:34,692 --> 00:12:37,862
It's 543-7, Shinyu-dong.
Get there by 11 p.m.

143
00:12:46,079 --> 00:12:47,455
For God's sake.

144
00:13:08,518 --> 00:13:10,645
Hayun, Mommy's right here.

145
00:13:15,483 --> 00:13:17,443
Yeah, Hayun, Mommy's right…

146
00:13:50,059 --> 00:13:51,519
[person] There's no time.

147
00:13:51,602 --> 00:13:53,396
I'm running out of time.

148
00:13:54,397 --> 00:13:58,776
When the girl in the red hood
gets swallowed by the snow…

149
00:13:59,652 --> 00:14:01,028
It's over.
STYLE
::cue()

150
00:14:06,909 --> 00:14:09,954
-Come on, Mom. Hurry!
-Oh, geez.

151
00:14:12,165 --> 00:14:15,168
This way. Over there.
He's on the second floor. Come on.

152
00:14:15,251 --> 00:14:17,587
ALWAYS WITH THE PEOPLE
SEONGJIN POLICE STATION

153
00:14:19,172 --> 00:14:20,173
Mom.

154
00:14:21,382 --> 00:14:27,096
Excuse me, we got a call
saying my son was being held here.

155
00:14:27,180 --> 00:14:29,765
-What's your son's name?
-Taeju. Kang Taeju.

156
00:14:29,849 --> 00:14:32,101
Mr. Kang is in interrogation
at the moment.

157
00:14:32,185 --> 00:14:33,477
-What?
-What?

158
00:14:33,561 --> 00:14:35,813
But my brother didn't do anything wrong.

159
00:14:35,897 --> 00:14:39,358
How's my brother the suspect
when his wife's been kidnapped?

160
00:14:39,442 --> 00:14:43,279
Look, sir.
My son would never commit a crime.

161
00:14:43,362 --> 00:14:45,489
This has to be a mistake.

162
00:14:45,573 --> 00:14:47,366
[Dr. Ko] It's not a mistake.

163
00:14:53,873 --> 00:14:55,458
Mr. Ko.

164
00:14:56,459 --> 00:14:58,127
I said, it's not a mistake.

165
00:15:05,218 --> 00:15:06,802
I'm a parent too.

166
00:15:08,554 --> 00:15:11,390
I know you must be heartbroken.

167
00:15:12,475 --> 00:15:14,644
But you know what my Taeju is like

168
00:15:15,186 --> 00:15:17,230
just as well as I do.

169
00:15:17,772 --> 00:15:21,484
Yeah, absolutely.
I know what kind of scum he is.

170
00:15:21,567 --> 00:15:26,489
The despicable kind that plotted
to have my daughter killed.

171
00:15:26,572 --> 00:15:27,615
Excuse me?

172
00:15:31,160 --> 00:15:33,913
I know this is hard, but that's just…

173
00:15:35,957 --> 00:15:38,334
I'd never say that to you, Mr. Ko.

174
00:15:38,834 --> 00:15:40,795
Don't even say my name, okay?

175
00:15:41,545 --> 00:15:45,675
It's my own damn fault for letting him
into my family in the first place!

176
00:15:45,758 --> 00:15:49,762
How are you so sure
that Taeju really did it?

177
00:15:49,845 --> 00:15:53,724
I saw with my own two eyes in that video,

178
00:15:53,808 --> 00:15:56,102
how he asked the guy
to get rid of my daughter!

179
00:15:56,185 --> 00:15:57,812
There's no way he did that.

180
00:15:57,895 --> 00:16:02,316
What, you think I'm lying to you
when my daughter's life is on the line?

181
00:16:05,528 --> 00:16:07,405
He's telling the truth.

182
00:16:09,573 --> 00:16:11,784
I saw the video with him.

183
00:16:36,559 --> 00:16:37,810
That's pretty.

184
00:17:12,678 --> 00:17:15,806
[door opens, closes]

185
00:17:18,100 --> 00:17:21,145
[footsteps approaching]

186
00:17:22,646 --> 00:17:26,025
[panting]

187
00:17:32,448 --> 00:17:33,532
[driver] Did you sleep well?

188
00:17:38,079 --> 00:17:41,457
I came by earlier,
but you were sleeping so soundly.

189
00:17:42,333 --> 00:17:44,835
How's your neck? Let me take a look.
STYLE
::cue()

190
00:17:47,880 --> 00:17:50,925
This is going to take a while to heal.

191
00:17:55,221 --> 00:17:56,972
[gasps]

192
00:17:57,556 --> 00:17:59,058
[driver] Here. Try putting this on it.

193
00:18:01,727 --> 00:18:03,187
LIQUID PAIN RELIEVER

194
00:18:03,938 --> 00:18:05,398
Come on, take it.

195
00:18:05,481 --> 00:18:07,108
You'll die when the time comes,

196
00:18:07,191 --> 00:18:09,360
so you might as well
spare yourself the pain now.

197
00:18:09,860 --> 00:18:11,070
Oh, well.

198
00:18:20,037 --> 00:18:22,081
This is how much time you have left.

199
00:18:27,044 --> 00:18:30,339
When the sand runs out, you're dead.

200
00:18:30,423 --> 00:18:32,842
[sobs, breathes heavily]

201
00:18:33,718 --> 00:18:36,137
-You all right?
-[screams, cries]

202
00:18:38,097 --> 00:18:39,682
[driver] Geez, okay.

203
00:18:42,017 --> 00:18:45,146
Right. Apparently, the nuns use this
when they pray at the convent.

204
00:18:45,229 --> 00:18:48,190
You should try praying
if you ever get bored.

205
00:18:49,400 --> 00:18:50,735
Who knows?

206
00:18:50,818 --> 00:18:54,363
You might impress God enough
to get you out of here.

207
00:18:54,864 --> 00:18:57,408
Why are you doing this to me?

208
00:19:01,287 --> 00:19:03,038
[sighs]

209
00:19:04,457 --> 00:19:07,001
[screams, pants]

210
00:19:07,084 --> 00:19:08,627
[sobbing]

211
00:19:09,170 --> 00:19:10,171
[driver] Use this, okay?

212
00:19:16,010 --> 00:19:18,971
Why are you doing this to me?

213
00:19:19,054 --> 00:19:21,599
What did I do to deserve this?

214
00:19:21,682 --> 00:19:24,393
What the hell do you want from me?

215
00:19:25,853 --> 00:19:28,731
[sobbing]

216
00:19:31,442 --> 00:19:32,568
[screams]

217
00:19:34,069 --> 00:19:35,780
[sobbing]

218
00:19:38,365 --> 00:19:42,286
[Dosik] That driver you'd never seen
before has probably gotten away by now.

219
00:19:43,996 --> 00:19:46,373
Until when do you plan on playing dumb?

220
00:19:48,417 --> 00:19:53,547
[stranger] If you want to find your wife,
come to 543-7, Shinyu-dong by 11 p.m.

221
00:19:58,761 --> 00:20:00,095
-[Dosik] Mr. Kang!
-[knocks on table]

222
00:20:01,180 --> 00:20:02,765
We need you to focus here!

223
00:20:08,979 --> 00:20:11,649
We found this in the trunk of your car.

224
00:20:12,483 --> 00:20:14,693
INSIDE THE TRUNK
OF THE SUSPECT'S VEHICLE

225
00:20:15,361 --> 00:20:16,987
Even the blood splatter matches.

226
00:20:17,613 --> 00:20:18,614
Isn't that funny?

227
00:20:19,532 --> 00:20:22,993
I mean, how could this
have made it into your car?

228
00:20:24,537 --> 00:20:26,497
[driver]
I said, did you bring my billion won?

229
00:20:41,846 --> 00:20:43,430
[sighs]

230
00:20:45,599 --> 00:20:46,642
I have no idea.

231
00:20:46,725 --> 00:20:47,726
[Dosik] "No idea," huh?

232
00:20:47,810 --> 00:20:50,980
You were there
when the photo was taken, weren't you?

233
00:20:52,565 --> 00:20:55,401
Obviously, he left it in my trunk
without me knowing.

234
00:20:55,484 --> 00:20:58,279
It's also obvious
that he sent you that email.

235
00:20:59,989 --> 00:21:01,198
Is that so?

236
00:21:01,282 --> 00:21:04,285
In that case,
where's the memory card for your dashcam?

237
00:21:04,368 --> 00:21:05,786
That'd prove your innocence.

238
00:21:06,912 --> 00:21:09,248
That's… It disappeared.

239
00:21:09,874 --> 00:21:12,751
Yeah. He probably took that too.

240
00:21:12,835 --> 00:21:16,422
Wow, such unfortunate timing, isn't it?

241
00:21:17,172 --> 00:21:21,218
People from the hospital
saw you arguing at the banquet.

242
00:21:22,636 --> 00:21:25,556
Don't tell me this is
a marriage problem gone too far.
STYLE
::cue()

243
00:21:26,557 --> 00:21:30,185
SEONGJIN POLICE STATION

244
00:22:02,843 --> 00:22:07,139
The moment we get the lab results back,
you're going to be detained.

245
00:22:08,724 --> 00:22:09,808
So come on.

246
00:22:10,309 --> 00:22:12,353
It's not too late to come clean.

247
00:22:13,395 --> 00:22:17,024
It's in your best interest
to keep Ms. Ko alive.

248
00:22:17,566 --> 00:22:18,651
Isn't that right?

249
00:22:28,702 --> 00:22:30,079
[line ringing]

250
00:22:30,162 --> 00:22:31,747
[phone buzzing]

251
00:22:37,419 --> 00:22:38,420
Do it now.

252
00:22:46,887 --> 00:22:48,013
[exclaims]

253
00:22:48,722 --> 00:22:50,933
What is going on today?

254
00:22:51,976 --> 00:22:53,185
[Hyeonsu] I'll go check it out.

255
00:22:55,521 --> 00:22:58,357
[Dosik sighs] Geez.

256
00:23:05,447 --> 00:23:06,448
[stranger] Remember.

257
00:23:06,949 --> 00:23:12,371
If you want to find your wife,
come to 543-7, Shinyu-dong by 11 p.m.

258
00:23:12,454 --> 00:23:13,497
If you don't,

259
00:23:13,580 --> 00:23:15,666
you may never get to see her again.

260
00:23:18,210 --> 00:23:19,878
What the… Kang Taeju.

261
00:23:21,171 --> 00:23:23,716
Hey, answer me! Kang Taeju!

262
00:23:27,094 --> 00:23:28,846
Can't they do anything about this?

263
00:23:36,729 --> 00:23:38,939
Hey, you know
we've got lines to the annex, right?

264
00:23:39,023 --> 00:23:40,524
-Yes, sir.
-Give them a call.

265
00:23:42,609 --> 00:23:44,028
Come on, man.

266
00:23:44,111 --> 00:23:45,738
Hey, go check out the annex building!

267
00:23:46,488 --> 00:23:48,282
I'll go check it out.

268
00:23:50,325 --> 00:23:52,036
Don't bother. I'll just call them.

269
00:23:57,249 --> 00:23:58,834
-Come over here.
-I'll check it out.

270
00:23:58,917 --> 00:24:00,419
-Kang Taeju!
-Hurry up…

271
00:24:00,502 --> 00:24:01,503
Get him!

272
00:24:02,838 --> 00:24:04,089
Hey, get that punk!

273
00:24:04,757 --> 00:24:06,175
He's going up!

274
00:24:07,968 --> 00:24:09,636
[officer] Get him now!

275
00:24:09,720 --> 00:24:11,638
[Dosik] Get him! Move it!

276
00:24:11,722 --> 00:24:13,474
Third floor! Get to the third floor!

277
00:24:13,557 --> 00:24:14,767
Kang Taeju!

278
00:24:26,945 --> 00:24:28,697
-You two take the right side.
-Yes, sir.

279
00:24:28,781 --> 00:24:30,991
You guys take the roof.
The rest of you, with me.

280
00:24:41,627 --> 00:24:43,879
[detective] Quick! Go up!

281
00:24:59,019 --> 00:25:00,687
-[Dosik] Did you see him?
-Negative.

282
00:25:03,190 --> 00:25:04,858
[exhales deeply]

283
00:25:06,151 --> 00:25:08,362
[panting]

284
00:25:19,248 --> 00:25:20,415
What about the rooftop?

285
00:25:20,499 --> 00:25:22,251
-Check out the main gate.
-[detective 1] Yes, sir.

286
00:25:22,334 --> 00:25:24,461
-Come on, let's hurry!
-[detective 2] We'll check it out!
STYLE
::cue()

287
00:25:41,770 --> 00:25:43,730
[panting]

288
00:25:56,869 --> 00:25:57,870
[grunts]

289
00:26:13,594 --> 00:26:18,015
So, guys, we've worked with
a lot of different codes so far, right?

290
00:26:18,098 --> 00:26:19,808
[students] Yeah!

291
00:26:19,892 --> 00:26:22,686
But see, you don't have to memorize
what every single code does

292
00:26:22,769 --> 00:26:24,354
or what you can do with it.

293
00:26:24,438 --> 00:26:27,816
The thing is,
even I don't have all of that memorized.

294
00:26:28,567 --> 00:26:29,943
-But Mr. Noh!
-[Mr. Noh] Yes?

295
00:26:30,027 --> 00:26:32,404
How can we use the codes
if we don't memorize them?

296
00:26:32,487 --> 00:26:33,989
Good point.

297
00:26:34,072 --> 00:26:37,534
When there's need, you can
look up the codes online to practice,

298
00:26:37,618 --> 00:26:41,038
or just let me know anytime you want.
You all have my number, right?

299
00:26:41,121 --> 00:26:42,664
[students] Yeah!

300
00:26:42,748 --> 00:26:45,792
All right, shall we check out
what we'll be learning today?

301
00:26:45,876 --> 00:26:47,377
Okay, turn to page 20.

302
00:27:22,287 --> 00:27:24,414
[knock on wall]

303
00:27:25,332 --> 00:27:26,917
[person] Are you feeling any better?

304
00:27:49,648 --> 00:27:50,941
I don't know.

305
00:27:52,234 --> 00:27:53,485
I'm telling you.

306
00:27:53,568 --> 00:27:55,904
It's going to get a lot worse.

307
00:27:55,988 --> 00:28:00,367
It only gets scarier
and more frightening over time.

308
00:28:01,076 --> 00:28:03,537
No one could ever get used to this.

309
00:28:04,454 --> 00:28:05,956
How did he get you?

310
00:28:06,498 --> 00:28:08,458
I got jumped from behind

311
00:28:08,542 --> 00:28:10,836
while I was leaving
a fortune teller's place.

312
00:28:11,586 --> 00:28:13,880
I was sleeping at home,

313
00:28:14,923 --> 00:28:17,342
and he was standing right there
when I opened my eyes.

314
00:28:18,719 --> 00:28:21,054
But I have no idea
why he's doing this to me.

315
00:28:21,555 --> 00:28:25,851
I think I have an idea
as to why this is happening to me.

316
00:28:26,935 --> 00:28:27,936
Why's that?

317
00:28:28,520 --> 00:28:31,648
See, I did a bad thing.

318
00:28:34,609 --> 00:28:36,028
"A bad thing"?

319
00:28:36,111 --> 00:28:41,158
There's a spirit we serve in our home,
and I turned my back on them.

320
00:28:42,075 --> 00:28:44,953
Things got so rough,
and I couldn't see a way forward,

321
00:28:45,037 --> 00:28:47,873
so I sought out
other shamans out of desperation.

322
00:28:49,124 --> 00:28:51,960
So maybe, do you think

323
00:28:53,503 --> 00:28:55,714
you might have wronged someone?

324
00:28:56,506 --> 00:28:58,175
Maybe you hurt someone.

325
00:28:59,384 --> 00:29:04,723
You know, being here really opened my eyes
to what a horrible thing I'd done.

326
00:29:10,854 --> 00:29:12,272
She's not praying.

327
00:29:17,277 --> 00:29:19,446
All right, guys. Everybody done reading?

328
00:29:19,529 --> 00:29:20,572
MR. NOH'S COMPUTER CLASS
STYLE
::cue()

329
00:29:34,753 --> 00:29:37,047
SEONGJIN POLICE STATION

330
00:29:43,887 --> 00:29:44,888
I found him!

331
00:29:48,558 --> 00:29:49,559
[Dosik] Play it back.

332
00:29:55,774 --> 00:29:57,109
He jumped out of that window?

333
00:29:57,734 --> 00:30:00,028
He's lost it. Isn't he a doctor?

334
00:30:00,695 --> 00:30:01,822
Are you admiring the guy?

335
00:30:02,781 --> 00:30:03,949
Get a move on.

336
00:30:04,032 --> 00:30:05,033
[Hyeonsu] Let's roll.

337
00:30:05,617 --> 00:30:06,868
Come on!

338
00:30:11,289 --> 00:30:13,250
Mom, here.

339
00:30:22,092 --> 00:30:23,176
Detective.

340
00:30:23,260 --> 00:30:25,554
What's going on? Where's Taeju?

341
00:30:25,637 --> 00:30:26,805
-He bolted.
-What?

342
00:30:26,888 --> 00:30:28,890
Wait a minute! What are you talking about?

343
00:30:28,974 --> 00:30:30,725
He ran off during the interrogation.

344
00:30:30,809 --> 00:30:32,227
-I…
-What…

345
00:30:33,478 --> 00:30:34,729
-What…
-What is going on?

346
00:30:34,813 --> 00:30:36,189
He ran away?

347
00:30:37,149 --> 00:30:41,236
You said your son is
incapable of doing anything bad.

348
00:30:41,319 --> 00:30:44,948
So why would he run
if he hasn't done anything wrong?

349
00:30:46,616 --> 00:30:49,161
I'm sure he had his reasons.

350
00:30:50,328 --> 00:30:51,955
Just give him some time.

351
00:30:52,038 --> 00:30:53,623
Reasons?

352
00:30:54,624 --> 00:30:56,960
There's no excuse
for running away from the police!

353
00:30:58,336 --> 00:30:59,379
My goodness.

354
00:31:00,088 --> 00:31:02,090
What a mother you are.

355
00:31:02,674 --> 00:31:05,093
What a loving mother!

356
00:31:05,177 --> 00:31:08,930
It's just incredible! Give me a break.

357
00:31:09,973 --> 00:31:11,057
[sighs]

358
00:31:12,809 --> 00:31:15,562
Oh, Mom. Are you okay?

359
00:31:16,479 --> 00:31:19,232
Let's sit you down. There you go.

360
00:31:19,316 --> 00:31:22,444
-Taeyeong.
-Yeah.

361
00:31:22,527 --> 00:31:25,322
-What in the world is happening?
-Exactly.

362
00:31:25,405 --> 00:31:27,407
-Why would he… Why…
-That idiot!

363
00:31:27,490 --> 00:31:30,619
Why did he run away
in a situation like this?

364
00:31:31,870 --> 00:31:33,163
Ugh, geez.

365
00:31:33,246 --> 00:31:34,331
It's okay.

366
00:31:35,582 --> 00:31:37,751
WOORI TOGETHER MEDICAL CENTER

367
00:32:04,027 --> 00:32:05,195
[elevator dings]

368
00:32:05,904 --> 00:32:07,155
Hey, excuse me.

369
00:32:08,073 --> 00:32:09,616
Oh, hey. It's just me.

370
00:32:09,699 --> 00:32:11,326
Oh, hello. Dr. Kang.

371
00:32:12,160 --> 00:32:13,578
What are you doing here so late?

372
00:32:15,580 --> 00:32:17,374
I forgot something in my office.

373
00:32:18,625 --> 00:32:20,418
-Have a good one.
-You too.

374
00:33:08,717 --> 00:33:10,427
OPERATING ROOM

375
00:33:13,680 --> 00:33:14,973
ACCESS GRANTED

376
00:33:15,056 --> 00:33:20,854
RESTRICTED AREA
AUTHORIZED PERSONNEL ONLY
STYLE
::cue()

377
00:34:30,006 --> 00:34:31,424
Geez, you scared me.

378
00:34:31,508 --> 00:34:34,344
-Hey, Chiung.
-What are you doing here so late?

379
00:34:34,427 --> 00:34:37,055
You know,
I just left something in the office.

380
00:34:38,181 --> 00:34:40,183
Must be pretty damn important.

381
00:34:40,850 --> 00:34:43,144
What about you? What are you doing here?

382
00:34:43,228 --> 00:34:45,146
I'm on call tonight.

383
00:34:45,230 --> 00:34:47,690
Pharmacy wanted me
to check the anesthetics inventory.

384
00:34:47,774 --> 00:34:49,484
I see.

385
00:34:50,318 --> 00:34:52,570
-Hang in there, then. See you.
-Okay.

386
00:34:54,948 --> 00:34:55,990
Chiung.

387
00:34:56,991 --> 00:34:57,992
[Dr. Choi] Hmm?

388
00:34:58,076 --> 00:34:59,703
What? You got something to say?

389
00:35:01,371 --> 00:35:02,455
Well, I…

390
00:35:03,498 --> 00:35:05,750
I had a bit of an incident today.

391
00:35:05,834 --> 00:35:07,043
Oh, what happened?

392
00:35:07,669 --> 00:35:10,046
Well, it's kind of serious.

393
00:35:11,089 --> 00:35:12,090
Yeah.

394
00:35:13,049 --> 00:35:15,427
Now that you mention it,
you're a mess, man.

395
00:35:15,510 --> 00:35:17,262
What's going on?

396
00:35:19,723 --> 00:35:20,765
It's nothing.

397
00:35:20,849 --> 00:35:22,100
I'll tell you later.

398
00:35:22,726 --> 00:35:26,438
You know, actually…
Could you lend me your car?

399
00:35:27,439 --> 00:35:29,774
My car? Where's yours?

400
00:35:30,608 --> 00:35:34,279
Mine's… What's with all the questions?
You'll get it back tomorrow.

401
00:35:35,321 --> 00:35:36,656
Yeah, whatever.

402
00:35:36,740 --> 00:35:38,324
It's on level B3.

403
00:35:40,535 --> 00:35:42,203
Is it something to do with your wife?

404
00:35:43,246 --> 00:35:44,247
It is, right?

405
00:35:45,290 --> 00:35:47,834
Something's going on, right? What is it?

406
00:35:52,547 --> 00:35:53,923
It's okay. You can tell me.

407
00:35:55,049 --> 00:35:56,259
The thing is…

408
00:35:57,761 --> 00:35:58,762
Seyun got…

409
00:35:58,845 --> 00:36:01,055
[phone ringing]

410
00:36:02,474 --> 00:36:04,017
Sorry, let me take this real quick.

411
00:36:06,728 --> 00:36:07,729
This is Choi.

412
00:36:10,356 --> 00:36:12,192
[Dr. Ko] Hey, Dr. Choi, it's me.

413
00:36:12,275 --> 00:36:14,194
I'll cut right to the chase.

414
00:36:14,277 --> 00:36:16,446
Have you heard from Taeju at all?

415
00:36:16,529 --> 00:36:18,948
-Yeah, what a coincidence.
-What?

416
00:36:19,032 --> 00:36:20,700
Are you with him right now?

417
00:36:22,243 --> 00:36:23,745
Answer with "yes" or "no" only.

418
00:36:25,288 --> 00:36:26,372
Yes.

419
00:36:29,751 --> 00:36:32,587
Where are you right now? At the hospital?

420
00:36:32,670 --> 00:36:33,671
Yes.

421
00:36:33,755 --> 00:36:35,590
Okay, he's at the hospital.

422
00:36:35,673 --> 00:36:38,343
I'll make the call to the police then.

423
00:36:38,426 --> 00:36:40,553
Listen to me carefully, Dr. Choi.

424
00:36:41,387 --> 00:36:44,808
That bastard kidnapped my daughter!

425
00:36:54,776 --> 00:36:56,110
What are you talking about?

426
00:36:56,194 --> 00:36:57,904
He’s got her hidden somewhere.

427
00:36:57,987 --> 00:37:01,199
He just bolted from the police station
while they were interrogating him!

428
00:37:02,283 --> 00:37:05,245
To find Seyun,
we have to catch that bastard.

429
00:37:06,162 --> 00:37:08,498
The police are on their way,

430
00:37:08,581 --> 00:37:10,917
so you have to keep him there,
no matter what.

431
00:37:11,000 --> 00:37:12,001
Do you hear me?

432
00:37:14,128 --> 00:37:15,505
Yeah, I got it.

433
00:37:16,422 --> 00:37:18,299
[grunts]

434
00:37:20,134 --> 00:37:23,888
Chiung, I'm so sorry. I'll explain later!

435
00:37:23,972 --> 00:37:25,723
Have you lost your mind?

436
00:37:26,683 --> 00:37:27,976
[groans]

437
00:37:29,185 --> 00:37:30,812
-Hey, who's there?
-Go, stop him.

438
00:37:30,895 --> 00:37:32,146
Dr. Choi?

439
00:37:33,147 --> 00:37:34,274
Dr. Choi!

440
00:37:34,357 --> 00:37:36,192
I said, go and stop Dr. Kang!

441
00:37:37,318 --> 00:37:38,528
Okay!

442
00:37:40,905 --> 00:37:42,365
[panting]

443
00:37:52,208 --> 00:37:53,459
[car chirps]

444
00:38:09,225 --> 00:38:10,476
-Hello.
-Dr. Kang.

445
00:38:10,560 --> 00:38:12,103
-What are you doing?
-Sorry.

446
00:38:12,186 --> 00:38:13,605
Just get out for a minute.

447
00:38:13,688 --> 00:38:15,732
-Right, yeah.
-We'll talk outside the car.

448
00:38:15,815 --> 00:38:18,234
-This seat belt just won't…
-Yeah, I'll do it for you.

449
00:38:18,318 --> 00:38:19,652
There we go. Come on.

450
00:38:19,736 --> 00:38:21,779
-No, listen, this is…
-It's just for a moment.

451
00:38:21,863 --> 00:38:24,616
-Look, Chief. You got it all wrong.
-I'm sure I do.
STYLE
::cue()

452
00:38:24,699 --> 00:38:25,700
I don't think so.

453
00:38:25,783 --> 00:38:28,077
-I understand.
-Could you… I said, you can't go.

454
00:38:28,161 --> 00:38:30,496
-I'll tell you later. I swear.
-Come on.

455
00:38:30,580 --> 00:38:31,581
I got it.

456
00:38:31,664 --> 00:38:35,084
I'll radio upstairs, so you can talk
after I hear from them. Stay right there.

457
00:38:38,338 --> 00:38:39,672
Dr. Kang!

458
00:38:39,756 --> 00:38:42,050
Stay away! [shouting]

459
00:38:42,967 --> 00:38:44,260
I'm so sorry!

460
00:38:44,344 --> 00:38:47,889
[tires squeal]

461
00:38:47,972 --> 00:38:49,933
Do your homework, Yuhyeon. Okay?

462
00:38:50,016 --> 00:38:51,100
-Okay, fine!
-Bye.

463
00:38:51,184 --> 00:38:53,561
-Bye.
-See you. [growls]

464
00:38:53,645 --> 00:38:55,772
-[phone buzzing]
-[vocalizes]

465
00:38:56,814 --> 00:38:57,815
Oh, hey, what's up?

466
00:39:02,320 --> 00:39:06,366
It's been blinking on and off
for the past few days,

467
00:39:06,449 --> 00:39:09,827
and now it's completely stopped working.

468
00:39:10,787 --> 00:39:14,415
[sighs] I couldn't take any payments.
It's really been a nightmare.

469
00:39:15,124 --> 00:39:16,292
What do you think?

470
00:39:16,376 --> 00:39:17,961
You think you can fix it?

471
00:39:18,044 --> 00:39:20,630
See. It's all the dust
that's built up in here.

472
00:39:20,713 --> 00:39:22,090
That's why it wouldn't read.

473
00:39:22,173 --> 00:39:24,133
-It should work now.
-Ah.

474
00:39:27,220 --> 00:39:28,221
There it is.

475
00:39:29,389 --> 00:39:32,642
My goodness! Now it works, huh?

476
00:39:32,725 --> 00:39:33,935
How much do I owe you?

477
00:39:34,018 --> 00:39:35,645
Oh, don't worry about it.

478
00:39:35,728 --> 00:39:39,399
Oh, come on. I feel bad
you help me out all the time.

479
00:39:39,482 --> 00:39:42,819
What's there to feel bad about?
Plus, who else would you get help from?

480
00:39:43,945 --> 00:39:46,990
Well, thank you.
Why don't you stay for dinner then?

481
00:39:47,573 --> 00:39:50,159
-Have a seat right here, okay?
-No, it's fine.

482
00:39:51,035 --> 00:39:53,121
-Come on. Have a seat. Okay?
-You don't have to.

483
00:39:55,373 --> 00:39:56,582
Thank you so much.

484
00:39:56,666 --> 00:39:59,794
JANG SUNDAEGUK

485
00:39:59,877 --> 00:40:02,422
Sweetheart, can you set his table?

486
00:40:02,505 --> 00:40:03,589
[grandchild] Okay, Grandma.

487
00:40:03,673 --> 00:40:06,009
Is that your granddaughter
you always talk about?

488
00:40:06,092 --> 00:40:07,301
Yes, she is.

489
00:40:12,223 --> 00:40:15,393
Your grandmother's told me all about you.

490
00:40:16,060 --> 00:40:17,395
-Nice to meet you.
-Likewise.

491
00:40:17,979 --> 00:40:22,483
You know Woori Together Medical Center?
She works as a nurse there.

492
00:40:23,109 --> 00:40:24,736
Oh.

493
00:40:24,819 --> 00:40:26,237
Yeah, I've been there.

494
00:40:26,320 --> 00:40:30,283
[owner] She helps me out
whenever she can, after her shift.

495
00:40:30,366 --> 00:40:33,619
She's not like
the other young people these days.

496
00:40:34,579 --> 00:40:36,039
I've raised a fine girl.

497
00:40:38,041 --> 00:40:40,460
You really have. You must be proud of her.

498
00:40:41,044 --> 00:40:43,796
Just sit tight,
and I'll get your food ready.

499
00:40:43,880 --> 00:40:45,423
-[Mr. Noh] Thank you.
-[laughs]

500
00:40:45,506 --> 00:40:47,633
[grandchild] That's 22,000 won.
Do you need your receipt?

501
00:40:47,717 --> 00:40:49,886
-[customer] It's fine.
-[on TV] Moving on to our next story…

502
00:40:49,969 --> 00:40:50,970
-[customer] Bye.
-Thank you.

503
00:40:51,054 --> 00:40:53,389
An armed robbery occurred
at a convenience store

504
00:40:53,473 --> 00:40:56,059
in Jungang-dong, Seongjin-gu,
around 8:40 tonight.

505
00:40:56,142 --> 00:40:59,562
Police took over 20 minutes to arrive
after receiving the report,

506
00:40:59,645 --> 00:41:01,397
allowing the suspect to escape.

507
00:41:01,481 --> 00:41:05,109
An unexplained power outage
at Seongjin Police Station

508
00:41:05,193 --> 00:41:08,154
disrupted communications,
delaying the initial response.
STYLE
::cue()

509
00:41:11,699 --> 00:41:14,577
[siren wailing]

510
00:41:14,660 --> 00:41:17,622
I mean, he did seem a little off
when he came in,

511
00:41:17,705 --> 00:41:19,457
but I didn't think much of it.

512
00:41:20,041 --> 00:41:24,253
And then Dr. Choi told me
to stop him, so I did.

513
00:41:24,337 --> 00:41:27,965
But then, Dr. Kang took my pepper gun
and sprayed me with it.

514
00:41:28,925 --> 00:41:30,843
My eyes haven't stopped watering since.

515
00:41:31,636 --> 00:41:32,678
[Dosik] You all right?

516
00:41:33,638 --> 00:41:35,139
Yeah, I'm fine.

517
00:41:36,015 --> 00:41:37,100
But…

518
00:41:37,183 --> 00:41:41,187
Listen. They're missing about six vials
of anesthetics in the operating room safe.

519
00:41:41,979 --> 00:41:43,439
They're missing some scalpels

520
00:41:43,523 --> 00:41:45,775
and surgical instruments
for cutting through bones.

521
00:41:46,359 --> 00:41:47,360
Right.

522
00:41:48,236 --> 00:41:50,363
When are you going to catch this bastard?

523
00:41:51,197 --> 00:41:53,908
What if something happens to my daughter?

524
00:41:53,991 --> 00:41:55,868
-Just a moment. Excuse me.
-[phone buzzes]

525
00:41:57,495 --> 00:41:58,496
Yes, talk.

526
00:41:59,038 --> 00:42:02,291
[Park] Yeah, Captain. It looks like
after carjacking the vehicle,

527
00:42:02,375 --> 00:42:04,877
Kang drove out of the parking garage
at 9:17 p.m.,

528
00:42:04,961 --> 00:42:07,171
and took a turn
toward Angok-ro at 9:18 p.m.

529
00:42:07,255 --> 00:42:08,714
He couldn't have gotten far then.

530
00:42:08,798 --> 00:42:12,176
Put out an APB on the vehicle
and have dispatch track him using WASS.

531
00:42:12,260 --> 00:42:14,554
Alert all nearby units for backup.

532
00:42:14,637 --> 00:42:16,806
-I'm moving out now.
-Copy that.

533
00:42:17,765 --> 00:42:20,017
It's go time. Let's roll.

534
00:42:23,938 --> 00:42:27,692
If you can't save my daughter,
I will hold you accountable.

535
00:42:28,442 --> 00:42:29,902
[Dosik] We'll do everything we can.

536
00:42:38,286 --> 00:42:39,453
Move it!

537
00:42:46,335 --> 00:42:48,421
-Head toward Angok-ro.
-Copy that.

538
00:42:51,799 --> 00:42:55,261
[siren wailing]

539
00:43:04,270 --> 00:43:05,688
[person] You bastard.

540
00:43:06,355 --> 00:43:07,857
You bastard.

541
00:43:08,608 --> 00:43:10,026
You bastard.

542
00:43:10,526 --> 00:43:11,652
You scumbag.

543
00:43:24,207 --> 00:43:25,708
[Seyun] You all right?

544
00:43:27,293 --> 00:43:29,128
He's such a bastard.

545
00:43:33,507 --> 00:43:34,508
Right.

546
00:43:36,969 --> 00:43:39,263
That's why he does these things.

547
00:43:40,640 --> 00:43:41,891
No, not him.

548
00:43:42,391 --> 00:43:43,726
I'm talking about my husband.

549
00:43:47,021 --> 00:43:48,022
What?

550
00:43:50,107 --> 00:43:53,194
The kidnapper called my husband
and told him I was kidnapped,

551
00:43:53,277 --> 00:43:56,781
but he just said, "Do whatever
you want with her" and hung up.

552
00:43:57,615 --> 00:43:59,533
He hasn't even picked up since.

553
00:44:05,748 --> 00:44:08,501
But the kidnapper
may not have been telling the truth.

554
00:44:09,335 --> 00:44:10,836
Maybe he made it all up.

555
00:44:12,588 --> 00:44:15,424
I had a fight
with my husband before I left.

556
00:44:16,133 --> 00:44:17,385
He said it to my face.

557
00:44:18,219 --> 00:44:20,763
That he was glad we didn't have children.

558
00:44:20,846 --> 00:44:23,349
That he wishes I would just die already.

559
00:44:25,059 --> 00:44:28,729
Me dying here is
exactly what he'd wish for.

560
00:44:29,981 --> 00:44:31,816
He'd be happy if I died.

561
00:44:32,984 --> 00:44:36,362
Was that your husband who was crying

562
00:44:37,071 --> 00:44:40,658
on the phone earlier?

563
00:44:49,583 --> 00:44:50,960
Yes, it was.
STYLE
::cue()

564
00:44:52,628 --> 00:44:55,798
You guys must have had
a good marriage going.

565
00:44:55,881 --> 00:44:58,509
We're both stuck here,
but I got to say, I'm jealous.

566
00:44:59,051 --> 00:45:00,303
[chuckles]

567
00:45:00,886 --> 00:45:02,054
What's your name?

568
00:45:03,347 --> 00:45:05,182
Mine's Lee Seonja.

569
00:45:07,935 --> 00:45:09,353
My name is Ko Seyun.

570
00:45:11,856 --> 00:45:13,482
Hey, Seyun.

571
00:45:13,566 --> 00:45:15,693
Can you do me a favor?

572
00:45:17,320 --> 00:45:18,321
What is it?

573
00:45:19,405 --> 00:45:21,657
When you get out of here,

574
00:45:22,491 --> 00:45:25,202
can you let the police know

575
00:45:25,286 --> 00:45:29,832
that Lee Seonja from Songmu-dong
died in this place?

576
00:45:31,667 --> 00:45:33,836
[crying] I don't have much time left.

577
00:45:34,503 --> 00:45:37,214
I'm going to die soon.

578
00:45:40,968 --> 00:45:42,970
[line ringing]

579
00:45:45,806 --> 00:45:47,850
[phone buzzing]

580
00:45:47,933 --> 00:45:49,518
PUBLIC SERVICE CENTER

581
00:45:52,521 --> 00:45:53,522
Hello?

582
00:45:53,606 --> 00:45:55,858
Taeyeong, it's me.

583
00:46:05,659 --> 00:46:06,660
You idiot.

584
00:46:07,787 --> 00:46:09,121
Where are you?

585
00:46:09,205 --> 00:46:10,414
What's going on?

586
00:46:10,998 --> 00:46:12,416
Why did you run away?

587
00:46:13,000 --> 00:46:15,753
I'll explain later.
How's Mom? Is she doing okay?

588
00:46:15,836 --> 00:46:17,296
Of course she isn't.

589
00:46:17,380 --> 00:46:19,215
She almost fainted because of you.

590
00:46:19,715 --> 00:46:21,926
Why would you run from the police?

591
00:46:22,635 --> 00:46:23,636
Hold on.

592
00:46:24,178 --> 00:46:25,262
It wasn't you, was it?

593
00:46:26,305 --> 00:46:27,348
Of course not.

594
00:46:28,933 --> 00:46:30,893
It wasn't me, but…

595
00:46:32,686 --> 00:46:34,605
She did get kidnapped because of me.

596
00:46:36,690 --> 00:46:38,567
I have to save Seyun.

597
00:46:38,651 --> 00:46:40,152
What are you talking about?

598
00:46:40,236 --> 00:46:42,363
You should be getting help
from the police.

599
00:46:42,446 --> 00:46:43,906
You can't do this on your own.

600
00:46:43,989 --> 00:46:46,367
You think you're some kind of superhero?

601
00:46:48,411 --> 00:46:49,412
Yeah.

602
00:46:50,746 --> 00:46:52,790
I kind of wish I was.

603
00:46:53,457 --> 00:46:54,500
Hey, listen.

604
00:46:55,167 --> 00:46:56,919
Talk to Mom for me, okay?

605
00:46:57,503 --> 00:46:59,422
Get back here and tell her yourself.

606
00:46:59,505 --> 00:47:02,508
If you didn't do it,
it'll all be revealed in time, right?

607
00:47:03,968 --> 00:47:05,803
Don't go making things worse, man.

608
00:47:05,886 --> 00:47:08,597
Listen to your big brother, Taeju. Okay?

609
00:47:11,016 --> 00:47:12,101
Taeju?

610
00:47:12,685 --> 00:47:13,769
Taeju.

611
00:47:16,105 --> 00:47:18,482
Taeju, where are you now?

612
00:47:19,024 --> 00:47:20,901
You're not hurt, are you?

613
00:47:21,444 --> 00:47:23,404
Hey, Mom. I'm fine.

614
00:47:26,031 --> 00:47:27,616
But I can't go back there right now.

615
00:47:27,700 --> 00:47:30,327
Seyun will be in more danger
if I stay at the station.

616
00:47:30,411 --> 00:47:32,037
What are you talking about?

617
00:47:32,121 --> 00:47:36,333
Why would you being at the station
put Seyun in danger?

618
00:47:36,876 --> 00:47:37,877
Taeju.

619
00:47:38,752 --> 00:47:40,254
Come back. It's not too late.

620
00:47:43,299 --> 00:47:44,300
Mom, just…

621
00:47:45,718 --> 00:47:49,430
Just trust me and give me some time.
I promise I'll bring Seyun home.

622
00:47:49,513 --> 00:47:51,557
Taeju.

623
00:47:52,224 --> 00:47:53,476
[call ends]

624
00:47:54,810 --> 00:47:55,895
[sobs]

625
00:47:55,978 --> 00:47:57,646
-Taeju…
-What is it, Mom?

626
00:47:57,730 --> 00:47:59,023
What did he say?

627
00:48:17,333 --> 00:48:19,335
RED LIGHT AND SPEEDING
SURVEILLANCE CAMERA

628
00:48:19,418 --> 00:48:21,962
[siren wailing]

629
00:48:22,922 --> 00:48:25,299
Captain, we got an update
on Kang's location.

630
00:48:25,382 --> 00:48:27,343
-Where?
-He was at Deoksam Intersection

631
00:48:27,426 --> 00:48:28,969
at 9:46 p.m.

632
00:48:29,053 --> 00:48:30,387
Heading that way.
STYLE
::cue()

633
00:48:41,899 --> 00:48:45,444
[panting]

634
00:49:12,137 --> 00:49:13,347
[grunts]

635
00:49:18,352 --> 00:49:21,188
[grunts, sighs]

636
00:49:42,293 --> 00:49:46,255
[grunting]

637
00:49:51,427 --> 00:49:52,928
[exclaims]

638
00:49:56,098 --> 00:49:58,726
[whimpers, exhales deeply]

639
00:50:05,608 --> 00:50:06,817
[strains]

640
00:50:48,359 --> 00:50:49,860
[strains]

641
00:50:50,694 --> 00:50:51,695
[grunts]

642
00:50:56,283 --> 00:50:57,534
It's working.

643
00:51:10,673 --> 00:51:13,634
[grunting]

644
00:51:58,721 --> 00:52:01,181
-Just make it quick.
-Yeah. We'd like to, but…

645
00:52:08,439 --> 00:52:11,191
Yujeong Intersection.
Plate number 682T 1228.

646
00:52:11,275 --> 00:52:12,818
Visual on suspect vehicle.

647
00:52:15,446 --> 00:52:16,447
Hey.

648
00:52:17,114 --> 00:52:18,282
Yujeong Intersection?

649
00:52:19,116 --> 00:52:20,117
Okay, on my way.

650
00:52:20,659 --> 00:52:22,619
Let's take the long way
through Shinyu-dong.

651
00:52:22,703 --> 00:52:23,704
Copy that.

652
00:52:23,787 --> 00:52:26,081
-Send backup to Yujeong Intersection.
-Sir.
STYLE
::cue()

653
00:52:26,665 --> 00:52:28,751
[Hyeonsu] Suspect vehicle
is on Yujeong Intersection.

654
00:52:28,834 --> 00:52:30,502
All nearby units, respond for backup.

655
00:52:51,356 --> 00:52:53,275
[siren wailing]

656
00:52:53,358 --> 00:52:55,986
[officer 1]
Plate number 1228, please pull over.

657
00:52:56,487 --> 00:52:58,238
Pull over, 1228.

658
00:52:58,822 --> 00:52:59,948
I repeat, 1228.

659
00:53:08,540 --> 00:53:11,210
I repeat. Pull over, 1228.

660
00:53:12,002 --> 00:53:14,421
I repeat, 1228. Stop the vehicle.

661
00:53:23,680 --> 00:53:24,890
[tires squeal]

662
00:53:28,310 --> 00:53:30,187
-[grunts]
-[horns honking]

663
00:53:36,193 --> 00:53:38,403
[officer 2] Suspect vehicle is heading
toward Shinyu-dong.

664
00:53:40,239 --> 00:53:42,241
Units two and three, in pursuit.

665
00:53:57,130 --> 00:53:58,257
[Dosik] Kang Taeju!

666
00:53:59,258 --> 00:54:00,592
Pull over right now!

667
00:54:00,676 --> 00:54:02,636
Stop the car, you bastard!
This is dangerous!

668
00:54:03,971 --> 00:54:05,138
Kang Taeju!

669
00:54:06,014 --> 00:54:07,307
Stop being so reckless!

670
00:54:10,060 --> 00:54:11,270
Pull over!

671
00:54:13,689 --> 00:54:14,690
Kang Taeju!

672
00:54:14,773 --> 00:54:16,441
Get in front of him.

673
00:54:17,109 --> 00:54:18,902
Cut him off! Get in front of him!

674
00:54:26,535 --> 00:54:28,161
Darn it.

675
00:54:49,683 --> 00:54:50,976
Turn around! Step on it!

676
00:54:51,059 --> 00:54:53,729
[officer 2] Control, we lost
the suspect vehicle during pursuit.

677
00:54:53,812 --> 00:54:55,230
Plate number 1228.

678
00:55:50,202 --> 00:55:52,329
[horn honks]

679
00:55:59,336 --> 00:56:00,587
Kang Taeju!

680
00:56:00,671 --> 00:56:03,173
Stop the car! Stop!

681
00:56:03,256 --> 00:56:05,008
You bastard!

682
00:56:05,092 --> 00:56:07,344
Hey! Kang Taeju!
STYLE
::cue()

683
00:57:01,982 --> 00:57:03,275
[gasps]

684
00:57:08,155 --> 00:57:10,824
[honking]

685
00:57:25,172 --> 00:57:26,673
[grunts]

686
00:58:41,706 --> 00:58:44,459
[breathes deeply]

687
00:58:50,340 --> 00:58:55,178
THE HUSBAND

688
00:58:55,262 --> 00:58:57,264
[♪ closing theme song playing]

689
00:59:35,302 --> 00:59:36,595
[Dosik] Put out an APB on Kang Taeju.

690
00:59:36,678 --> 00:59:39,139
[reporter] A standoff erupted
between police and a neurosurgeon

691
00:59:39,222 --> 00:59:43,435
suspected of orchestrating
his wife's kidnapping and murder.

692
00:59:43,518 --> 00:59:45,937
What the hell? Where is my wife?

693
00:59:46,021 --> 00:59:48,565
-Answer me!
-It's up to you to figure it out now.

694
00:59:48,648 --> 00:59:50,150
[Taeju] Are you working with that bastard?

695
00:59:51,526 --> 00:59:56,907
[Mr. Noh] I know exactly what you're
thinking and doing, wherever you are.

696
00:59:56,990 --> 00:59:58,700
[stranger]
Have you ever killed a person before?

697
00:59:58,783 --> 01:00:01,202
For his wife…

698
01:00:01,286 --> 01:00:02,871
Could Kang Taeju kill a person?

699
01:00:02,954 --> 01:00:04,331
Are you out of your mind?

700
01:00:04,414 --> 01:00:07,292
[Taeju] The three billion you have here.
I need you to hand it over to me.

701
01:00:08,293 --> 01:00:10,295
Translated by Hyun Sik Yoon

